For the moment, we are working on the release of the next version **2.9.7** of \G'MIC (see the current state of the [ _changelog_ ](https://discuss.pixls.us/t/on-the-road-to-3-0/)).

We already had a lot of __exciting news__ lately :

  - A few new image processing filters to play with.
  - Our plug-in G'MIC-Qt is now supported on [GIMP](https://www.gimp.org) __2.99__ (development version of GIMP 3), as well as on [Photoshop](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adobe_Photoshop), [Affinity Photo](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Affinity_Photo), and theoretically all 8bf-compatible hosts (thanks to [*Jan Tojnar*](https://github.com/jtojnar) and [*Nicholas Hayes*](https://github.com/0xC0000054) who made this possible!).
  - And of course, a lot of bugfixes (that we do not always make appear in the _changelog_ :) ).

We now focus on the fixing the few remaining bugs, to have a really cool **2.9.7** version to propose soon (hopefully).

#### So, until we can announce the release of this new version, we thank you again!


#### Stay safe!